OL,3,CGovernment apologises to DES drug
OL,4,Cvictims after ITV News investigation
OL,6,FThis is the first time health
OL,7,Fauthorities have publicly recognised
OL,8,Fthe harm caused by DES, after our
OL,9,Finvestigation exposed that warnings
OL,10,Fabout the sinister side effects of the
OL,11,Fdrug were not acted on for decades.
OL,13,FIn the letter seen by ITV News, Mr
OL,14,FStreeting wrote: "I am genuinely sorry
OL,15,Fthat women and their families have
OL,16,Fsuffered for too long.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
