OL,6,FIn September 2025, the regulator
OL,7,Fadmitted that information was
OL,8,Fincorrect, and the drug was not
OL,9,Fstopped for use in pregnancy until the
OL,10,F1980s, more than a decade after cancer
OL,11,Frisks were known.
OL,13,FDES, originally called
OL,14,FDiethylstilboestrol, is a synthetic
OL,15,Foestrogen invented in Britain in 1939.
OL,16,FResearch suggests pregnant women who
OL,17,Ftook DES may have a 30% higher risk of
OL,18,Fbreast cancer.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/16
